=Introduction

    This is a conlang project. My rough "goal" in creating this is to make a
more phonologically and morphologically complex constructed language than I've
done in the past, and translate some things into it. This is mainly so that I
have an excuse to experiment with interesting (and maybe some unfamiliar)
linguistic features.
    The name "Unnamic" is derived from the word "unnamed"; modified with the
"-ic" suffix and Proper-Noun'd with a capital "U". "Unnamic" is the English name
for the language, i.e. an exonym, and not the native name for it.
    This page will serve as the official documentation for my conlang.

